// Read-path field exposure: a customer's `loyalty_tier` must travel on the
// public-profile read path -- it is included in the read projection (the
// `.values(...)` column set the profile query asks for) AND returned in the
// API response shape. The exposure site is `read_public_profile` /
// `render_public_profile` in code/app/services/customers_profile.py. This is
// the reliably code-derivable core of "the tier reaches the consumer" -- a
// projection + response SITE, not prop threading through named files.

field-exposure customer.loyalty-tier-exposed {
  origin "reference/specs/modules/customers/data.md" "Customer read projection" 43..50
  field Entity:Customer.loyalty_tier
  via query-select
  via api-response
  in read_public_profile
}
